 Tree
 
 Writhing and wriggling in the whistling wind
 Shaking soundly while shielding the sun
 Fearlessly foliating, until a ferocious fall
 Losing leaves with lightning liberation
 Bending not breaking, holding with bulldog tenacity
 
 -JC '95
